cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper explores the use of motion for robot-to-human communication on three different robotic platforms, which suggests that it could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the accuracy, time, and confidence of user interactions, which could fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of a camera gimbal and the evaluation of visual interactions could also place this paper in the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The development of kineme systems and the prescription for further development could be considered Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Systems and Control (cs.SY).
